                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/9714: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-07T21:00:00+03:00"
                            >April 7, 1941—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 7—6:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>704. It has been reported to the Embassy, based on first hand information, that
                    quiet recruiting is now progressing in Moscow and that engineering students have
                    also been mobilized quietly and dispatched to the German frontier for the
                    purpose of erecting defense works there.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
